%N A051338 Generalized Stirling number triangle of first kind read by rows: T(n, k) = [x^k] Product_{m=1..n} (x - m - r), with r = 5.
%C A051338 T(n, m) = ^6P_n^m in the notation of the given reference with T(0, 0) = 1.
%C A051338 The monic row polynomials s(n, x) = Sum_{m=0..n} T(n, m)*x^m which are s(n, x) = Product_{k=0..n-1} x-(6+k), n >= 1 and s(0, x) = 1 satisfy s(n, x+y) = Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(n, k)*s(k, x)*S1(n-k, y), with the Stirling1 polynomials S1(n, x) = Sum_{m=1..n} A008275(n, m)*x^m and S1(0, x) = 1. In the umbral calculus (see the S. Roman reference given in A048854) the s(n, x) polynomials are called Sheffer for (exp(6*t), exp(t)-1).
%H A051338 Reinhard Zumkeller, <a href="/A051338/b051338.txt">Rows n = 0..125 of triangle, flattened</a>
%H A051338 Dragoslav S. Mitrinović and Ružica S. Mitrinović, <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240330150814/http://pefmath2.etf.rs/files/47/77.pdf">Tableaux d'une classe de nombres reliés aux nombres de Stirling</a>, Univ. Beograd. Pubi. Elektrotehn. Fak. Ser. Mat. Fiz. 77 (1962); <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/43667130">alternative link</a>.
%F A051338 T(n, m) = T(n-1, m-1) - (n+5)*T(n-1, m), n >= m >= 0; T(n, m) = 0, n < m; T(n, -1) = 0, T(0, 0) = 1.
%F A051338 E.g.f. for m-th column of signed triangle: ((log(1+x))^m)/(m!*(1+x)^6).
%F A051338 Triangle (signed) = [ -6, -1, -7, -2, -8, -3, -9, -4, -10, ...] DELTA A000035; triangle (unsigned) = [6, 1, 7, 2, 8, 3, 9, 4, 10, 5, 11, ...] DELTA A000035; where DELTA is Deléham's operator defined in A084938.
%F A051338 If we define f(n, i, a) = Sum_{k=0..n-i} binomial(n,k)*stirling1(n-k,i)*Product_{j=0..k-1}(-a-j), then T(n, i) = f(n, i, 6), for n=1,2,...; i=0..n. - _Milan Janjic_, Dec 21 2008
